{"title_page": "COVID-19 pandemic in Mexico", "text_new": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Ongoing COVID-19 viral pandemic in Mexico}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2020}}\n{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = COVID-19 pandemic in Mexico\n| map1            = {{Switcher\n|[[file:COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Mexico.svg|200xpx]]\n| Number of cumulative confirmed cases by state\n|[[file:COVID-19 Outbreak Active Cases in Mexico.svg|200xpx]]\n| Number of active confirmed cases by state\n|[[file:COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Mexico per 100,000 inhabitants.svg|200xpx]]\n| Cumulative cases per 100,000 inhabitants by state \n|[[file:COVID-19 Outbreak Active Cases in Mexico per 100,000 inhabitants.svg|200xpx]]\n| Active cases per 100,000 inhabitants by state | default = 1\n}}\n| legend1         = <center>Confirmed cases (as of April 30)</center>\n| map2            = COVID-19 Outbreak Deaths in Mexico.svg\n| legend2         = Number of confirmed deaths by state\n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = Mexico\n| first_case      = [[Mexico City]] and [[Los Mochis]]<ref name=\"First\" />\n| arrival_date    = February 28, 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=02|day1=28|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China<br /> (via Italy and the United States)<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Confirman-siete-casos-de-coronavirus-en-Mexico-20200307-0085.html |title= Confirman siete casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |language=Spanish |work=informador.mx |date=March 7, 2020 |access-date=March 17, 2020}}</ref>\n| recovery_cases  = 11,423 <small>({{As of|2020|05|01}})</small><ref>{{cite web |url=  https://www.debate.com.mx/salud/Suman-3087-pacientes-recuperados-de-coronavirus-en-Mexico-20200419-0234.html |title= Suman 3,087 pacientes recuperados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |language=Spanish |work=debate.com.mx |date=April 19, 2020 |access-date=April 24, 2020}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 2,271\n| confirmed_cases = 24,905\n| active_cases    = 6,696\n| suspected_cases = 13,143\n| severe_cases    = 1,735 <small>(severe)</small><br/> 378 <small>(mechanical ventilation)</small><ref name=\"cases1\" />\n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|https://coronavirus.gob.mx/}}\n}}\nThe [[COVID-19 pandemic]] was confirmed to have reached [[Mexico]] in February 2020. However, the [[Consejo Nacional de Ciencia y Tecnolog\u00eda (Mexico)|National Council of Science and Technology (CONACYT)]] reported two cases of COVID-19 in mid-January 2020 in the states of Nayarit and Tabasco, one case per state.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://datos.covid-19.conacyt.mx/#COMNac |title=Covid-19 CONACYT |date= April 21, 2020 |language=es}}</ref> As of May 4, there had been 24,905 confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Mexico and 2,271 reported deaths,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/mexico-registra-mas-de-24-mil-casos-por-coronavirus-suman-2-271-muertes |title=Asciende a 2,271 la cifra de fallecidos por coronavirus; van 24,905 casos. |author= Redacci\u00f3n |date= May 4, 2020 |language=es |website= El Financiero}}</ref> although the Secretariat of Health estimated, in mid April 2020, that there were more than 26,000 cases in Mexico, because they were considering the total number of cases confirmed as a statistical sample.<ref name=\"sentinela\" />\n\n== Background ==\nOn January 12, 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on December 31, 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archivedate=January 30, 2020|accessdate=March 15, 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=March 4, 2020 |work=Wired UK|accessdate=March 5, 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archivedate=March 5, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=March 15, 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=March 19, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=March 3, 2020|access-date=March 17, 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=March 12, 2020|access-date=March 15, 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n== Timeline ==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Mexico medical cases chart}}\n\n=== January 2020 ===\nOn January 22, 2020, the [[Secretariat of Health (Mexico)|Secretariat of Health]] issued a statement saying that the novel coronavirus COVID-19 did not present a danger to Mexico. 441 cases had been confirmed in [[COVID-19 pandemic in mainland China|China]], [[COVID-19 in Thailand|Thailand]], [[COVID-19 pandemic in South Korea|South Korea]], and [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United States|the United States]], and a travel advisory was issued on January 9.<ref name=indigo />\n\nOn January 30, 2020 before the declaration of a pandemic by the [[World Health Organization]] the Government of Mexico designed a ''Preparation and Response Plan'' that was made by the National Committee for Health Safety, a working group led by Secretariat of Health composed by different health entities aiming to act upon the imminent arrival of the pandemic. This group carried out a series of alert measures, rehabilitation and updating of epidemiological regulations based on the International Health Regulations, being the first Latam country that deployed a [[mathematical modelling of infectious disease]].<ref name=salud />\n\n=== February 2020 ===\nThe cruise ship ''[[Grand Princess]]'' docked in [[Puerto Vallarta]] (February 15), [[Manzanillo, Colima|Manzanillo]] (February 16), [[Mazatl\u00e1n]] (February 17) and [[Cabo San Lucas]](February 18), spending 9 to 12 hours in each port. The first COVID-19 death in California was a man who had been on this ship on an earlier cruise. This ship was later quarantined off San Francisco and docked in Oakland March 11 with 21 onboard who tested positive for the coronavirus.<ref>[https://www.latimes.com/california/story/2020-03-09/what-we-know-about-grand-princess-docking-coronavirus-quarantine What we know about Grand Princess docking] Los Angeles Times</ref>\n\nThe cruise ship {{ship||MSC Meraviglia}}, which was not allowed to dock in the [[COVID-19 pandemic in the Cayman Islands|Cayman Islands]] or [[COVID-19 pandemic in Jamaica|Jamaica]], docked in [[Cozumel]], Quintana Roo, on February 27. Three passengers were diagnosed with ''[[influenza A virus]],'' but no cases of coronavirus were found.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://politica.expansion.mx/mexico/2020/02/26/el-crucero-que-arribo-a-cozumel-esta-libre-de-coronavirus |title=El crucero que arrib\u00f3 a Cozumel est\u00e1 libre de coronavirus |trans-title=The cruise ship that arrived in Cozumel is free of coronaviruses |language=es |work=Expansi\u00f3n Politica |date=February 27, 2020 |access-date=March 14, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn February 28, Mexico confirmed its first three cases. A 35-year-old man and a 59-year-old man in [[Mexico City]] and a 41-year-old man in the northern state of [[Sinaloa]] tested positive and were held in isolation at a hospital and a hotel, respectively. They had travelled to [[Bergamo]] and stayed in Italy for a week in mid-February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://losangeles.cbslocal.com/2020/02/28/mexico-confirms-its-first-2-coronavirus-cases/|title=Mexico Confirms Its First 2 Coronavirus Cases|last=|first=|date=February 28, 2020|website=CBS Los Angeles |url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=February 28, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20200228134645-auoh9/|title=Mexico confirms first coronavirus cases in two men returned from Italy|last=Foundation|first=Thomson Reuters|website=news.trust.org|access-date=February 28, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"First\">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/GobiernoMX/status/1233418133353844736|title=La @SSalud_mx confirm\u00f3 dos casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico, el primero en la capital y el segundo en Sinaloa. Se trata de pacientes de bajo riesgo que est\u00e1n siendo atendidos. Invitamos a la poblaci\u00f3n a seguir informada y tomar medidas de prevenci\u00f3n|last=M\u00e9xico|first=Gobierno de|date=February 28, 2020|website=@GobiernoMX|language=es|access-date=February 28, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/van-3-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico|title=Van 3 casos confirmados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico|website=El Financiero|language=es|access-date=February 29, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn February 29, a fourth case was detected and confirmed in the city of [[Torre\u00f3n]], in the state of [[Coahuila]], from a 20-year-old woman who traveled to Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.milenio.com/estados/coronavirus-torreon-confirma-miguel-riquelme-caso-covid19|title=Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: lo \u00faltimo del nuevo caso en Torre\u00f3n|website=milenio.com|accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== March 2020 ===\n==== March 1 to 15====\nOn March 1, a fifth case was announced in [[Chiapas]] in a student who had just returned from Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnoticias.mx/confirman-caso-de-coronavirus-en-chiapas/159656|title=Confirman caso de coronavirus en Chiapas|website=ABC Noticias|language=es|date=March 1, 2020|accessdate=March 1, 2020}}</ref> On March 6, a sixth case was confirmed in the [[State of Mexico]] in a 71-year-old man who had returned from Italy on February 21.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://politica.expansion.mx/mexico/2020/03/06/confirman-sexto-caso-de-coronavirus-en-el-estado-de-mexico|title=La Secretar\u00eda de Salud confirma el sexto caso de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico|date=March 7, 2020|website=ADNPol\u00edtico|accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\nCOVID-19 was the topic of conversation at the meeting of the National Governors' Conference (Conago) held on March 5, 2020. In addition to governors from different states (or state health representatives), the directors of [[Instituto de Salud para el Bienestar|Instituto de Salud para el Bienestar (INSABI)]], [[Mexican Social Security Institute|IMSS]], and [[Institute for Social Security and Services for State Workers|ISSSTE]] participated.<ref name=conago>[https://www.elsoldecuernavaca.com.mx/local/analizan-gobernadores-situacion-del-coronavirus-4928720.html Governors analyze the situation of Coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} by Miriam Estrada, ''El Sol de Cuernavaca'', March 5, 2020, retrieved March 16, 2020</ref>\n\nOn March 6 during the first session of National Council of Health, [[Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell Ram\u00edrez]], one of the main strategists and spokespersons of Mexican Government on pandemics, led the first daily press conference on Covid-19.<ref name=nat_coun_health>{{Citation|title=Conferencia de prensa. Informe diario sobre coronavirus COVID-19 en M\u00e9xico. Secretar\u00eda de Salud|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZruOELSa7vA|language=en|access-date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 7, a seventh case was also confirmed in [[Mexico City]] in a 46-year-old male who had previously had contact with another confirmed case in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reporteindigo.com/reporte/confirman-el-septimo-caso-de-coronavirus-en-mexico/|title=Se eleva a 7 el n\u00famero de casos confirmados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico|accessdate=March 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 10, an eighth case was reported in [[Puebla (state)|Puebla]], a 47-year-old German man who had returned from a business trip to Italy.<ref name=\"8 cases\">{{cite web |first1=|title=Puebla reporta primer caso positivo de coronavirus |url=https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/proveedor-aleman-de-volkswagen-dio-positivo-a-coronavirus-secretaria-de-salud-de-puebla |website=El Financiero |publisher=Cuartoscuro |accessdate=March 11, 2020}}</ref> On the same date, 40 members of a dance company in Puebla, returning from a tour in Italy, were quarantined.<ref name=\"Ballet Ce Acatl\">{{cite web |last1=Arellano Garc\u00eda |first1=Cesar |title=Supervisar\u00e1n salud de ballet folkl\u00f3rico que vuelve de Italia |url=https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/10/supervisaran-salud-de-ballet-folklorico-que-vuelve-de-italia-4751.html |website=La Jornada |publisher=La Jornada |accessdate=March 11, 2020|date=March 10, 2020 }}</ref> The [[Mexican Stock Exchange]] fell to a record low on March 10 due to fears of the coronavirus and because of falling oil prices. The [[Bank of Mexico|Bank of Mexico (Banxico)]] stepped in to prop up the value of the peso, which fell 14% to 22.929 per US dollar.<ref name=banixco>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexicos-stock-market-hits-record-low-over-coronavirus-crisis-and-collapsing-oil-prices Mexico's stock market hits record low over coronavirus crisis and collapsing oil prices] {{in lang|en}} ''El Universal'' (English), March 10, 2020</ref>\n\nOn March 11, a ninth case was confirmed in the city of [[Monterrey]], [[Nuevo Le\u00f3n]]. A 57-year-old man, who had recently come back from a trip all across Europe, was placed under quarantine. The man, who has remained anonymous, came back from his trip a week before and had contact with eight other people who have also been placed under quarantine in their houses. The man has been confirmed to reside in the city of [[San Pedro Garza Garc\u00eda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mty.telediario.mx/local/confirman-el-primer-caso-de-coronavirus-en-nuevo-leon|title=Confirman el primer caso de coronavirus en Nuevo Le\u00f3n|date=March 11, 2020|website=Telediario Monterrey|language=es|access-date=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 12, Mexico announced it had a total of 15 confirmed cases, with new cases in [[Puebla]] and [[Durango]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.msn.com/es-mx/noticias/mexico/ya-son-15-casos-de-coronavirus-en-m%C3%A9xico-hay-82-sospechosos/ar-BB117yPi?ocid=msedgntp|title=Ya son 15 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 82 sospechosos|website=msn.com|access-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref> A day later, senator {{ill|Samuel Garc\u00eda Sep\u00falveda|es}} accused the federal government of hiding the true number of confirmed cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sdpnoticias.com/local/nuevo-leon/gobierno-de-mexico-esconde-cifras-coronavirus-pandemia-samuel-garcia.html |title=Gobierno de M\u00e9xico ESCONDE cifras reales de CORONAVIRUS, acusa Samuel Garc\u00eda|last=SDPnoticias.com|website=SDPnoticias.com |language=spanish|access-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 13, it was confirmed that the [[Mexican Stock Exchange]] Chairman, [[Jaime Ruiz Sacristan]], tested positive as an asymptomatic case.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/da-positivo-de-coronavirus-el-presidente-de-la-bolsa-mexicana-jaime-ruiz-sacristan|title=Da positivo de coronavirus el presidente de la Bolsa Mexicana, Jaime Ruiz Sacrist\u00e1n|website=El Financiero|language=es|access-date=March 13, 2020}}</ref> Later, the Secretariat of Health announced in press conference that the number of confirmed cases had risen to 26.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Espino |first1=Manuel |title=M\u00e9xico suma 26 casos positivos de coronavirus |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-13-de-marzo-mexico-suma-26-casos-positivos-de-coronavirus |website=El Universal |date=March 14, 2020 |publisher=El Universal, compa\u00f1\u00eda period\u00edstica Nacional |accessdate=March 14, 2020 |ref=March 13, 26 cases}}</ref> Several universities, including the [[National Autonomous University of Mexico|UNAM]] and [[Monterrey Institute of Technology and Higher Education|Tec de Monterrey]], switched to virtual classes. Authorities announced to be considering the cancellation of the ''Festival Internacional de Cine de Guadalajara''. In M\u00e9rida, the ''Tianguis Tur\u00edstico'' was postponed to September. Several major sporting events were also canceled.<ref name=cancelations>{{cite web |url=https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Suspenden-actividades-masivas-por-coronavirus-20200313-0020.html |title=Suspenden actividades masivas por coronavirus |trans-title=Massive Suspension of Activities Due to Coronavirus |language=Spanish |work=Informador.mx |date=March 13, 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Student during Coronavirus in Mexico (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|As part of the suspension of academic activities decreed by the SEP, students of all levels began taking classes online.]]\nOn March 14, [[Fernando Petersen]], the secretary of health of the state of [[Jalisco]], confirmed the first two cases of COVID-19 were detected in Hospital Civil de [[Guadalajara]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.informador.mx/jalisco/Confirman-primeros-dos-casos-de-coronavirus-en-Jalisco-20200314-0052.html|title=Confirman primeros dos casos de coronavirus en Jalisco|website=El Informador: Noticias de Jalisco, M\u00e9xico, Deportes & Entretenimiento|language=es-ES|access-date=March 14, 2020}}</ref> Two new cases were confirmed in Nuevo Le\u00f3n, and the [[Secretariat of Public Education (Mexico)|Secretariat of Public Education (SEP)]] announced that all sporting and civic events in schools would be canceled.<ref name=sep>{{cite web |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-sep-cancela-eventos-deportivos-y-civicos-en-escuelas |title=SEP cancela eventos deportivos y c\u00edvicos en escuelas por coronavirus |trans-title=SEP cancels sporting and civic events in schools due to coronavirus |language=Spanish |work=El Universal |date=March 14, 2020}}</ref> The same day, the Secretariat of Education announced that Easter break, originally planned from April 6 to 17, would be extended from March 20 to April 20 as a preventive measure.<ref name=\"Prevention Easter break in schools\">{{cite web |last1=Huizache |first1=Dolores |title=SEP anuncia que vacaciones de Semana Santa se adelantan por coronavirus |url=https://www.am.com.mx/noticias/SEP-anuncia-que-vacaciones-de-Semana-Santa-se-adelantan-por-coronavirus-20200314-0021.html |website=AM Mexico |publisher=EDITORIAL MARTINICA S.A. DE C.V. |accessdate=March 14, 2020}}</ref> The [[Secretariat of Finance and Public Credit|Secretariat of Finance and Public Credit (SCHP)]] announced it was taking measures to prevent a 0.5% fall in [[Gross domestic product |gross domestic product (GDP)]].<ref name=schp>{{cite web |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/cartera/listo-paquete-contraciclico-para-impulsar-economia |title=Por Covid-19, Hacienda tiene plan contrac\u00edclico |trans-title=Because of coronavirus, Treasury has a countercyclical package ready to boost economy |work=El Universal |date=March 14, 2020 |access-date=March 16, 2020}}</ref> Drugstores in [[Cuernavaca]] report shortages of masks, antibacterial gel, and other items.<ref>[https://www.elsoldecuernavaca.com.mx/local/comienzan-a-escasear-productos-por-covid-19-4971890.html Products start to be scarce due to COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} Jessica Arellano, ''El Sol de Cuernavaca'', March 14, 2020</ref> On the same day the [[Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de Nuevo Le\u00f3n|Autonomous University of Nuevo Leon, (UANL)]] (the country's third largest university in terms of student population) suspended classes for its more than 206,000 students starting on March 17 and ending on April 20.<ref name=uanl>{{cite web |last1=Garza|first1=Aracely|title= Universidad Aut\u00f3noma de NL suspende clases por Covid-19|language=es|trans-title=Autonomous University of NL suspends classes because of Covid-19|url= https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/universidad-autonoma-de-nl-suspende-clases-por-covid-19/1369792 |website=Exc\u00e9lsior |date=March 14, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Garza|first1=Aracely|language=es|title= Suspende UANL clases virtuales |url= https://m.imagenradio.com.mx/suspende-uanl-clases-virtuales |website=Imagen Radio |date=March 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\nBusinessman Jos\u00e9 Kuri was reported in critical condition on March 14 after a trip to [[Vail, Colorado]], United States, although early reports of his death were false.<ref>{{cite web|website=El Sol de M\u00e9xico|title=El empresario Jos\u00e9 Kuri se encuentra en estado cr\u00edtico a causa de coronavirus|trans-title=The businessman Jos\u00e9 Kuri is in critical condition due to coronavirus|language=es|date=March 15, 2020|accessdate=March 16, 2020|author=EFE|url=https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/mexico/sociedad/el-empresario-jose-kuri-se-encuentra-en-estado-critico-a-causa-de-coronavirus-4974999.html}}</ref> As of March 14, there have been 41 confirmed cases of [[COVID-19]] in Mexico.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://politica.expansion.mx/presidencia/2020/03/14/mexico-llega-a-41-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-con-155-sospechosos |title=M\u00e9xico llega a 41 casos confirmados de coronavirus, con 155 casos sospechosos |work=expansion.mx |language=Spanish |date=March 14, 2020 |access-date=March 16, 2020|trans-title=Mexico has 41 confirmed and 155 suspected cases of coronavirus}}</ref>\n\nThe March 14 and 15 ''[[Vive Latino|Festival Vive Latino]]'' (rock and Latin music) in Mexico City opened according to schedule, in spite of fears of contagion. Temperatures of the 70,000 people who attend each day were taken at the door and anti-bacterial gel was widely distributed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/14/el-coronavirus-avanza-apresurado-en-mexico-y-las-pruebas-de-detencion-cuestan-hasta-18000-pesos/ |title=El coronavirus avanza apresurado en M\u00e9xico y las pruebas de detecci\u00f3n cuestan hasta 18,000 pesos |trans-title=Coronavirus rushes ahead in Mexico and screening tests cost up to 18,000 pesos |language=Spanish |work=Infobae |date=March 14, 2020 |access-date=March 16, 2020}}</ref> Organizers said that the ''[[Passion Play of Iztapalapa]]'' would continue as scheduled in Holy Week. Tito Dom\u00ednguez, vice president of the organizing committee, noted that a miracle had saved Iztapalapa during the [[Cholera outbreaks and pandemics|cholera outbreak in 1833]].<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/pasion-de-cristo-en-iztapalapa-podria-cancelarse-debido-al-covid-19-coronavirus-claudia-sheinbaum-iglesia-catolica-pasion-de-cristo-coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-4974131.html Coronavirus will not stop the Stations of the Cross in Iztapalapa: organizing committee] {{in lang|es}} Maleny Navarro, ''El Sol de M\u00e9xico''. March 15, 2020</ref>\n\nOn March 15, Head of Government [[Claudia Sheinbaum]] stated that Mexico City expects to spend an extra MXN $100 million (US$4.4 million) to prevent the spread of COVID-19.<ref name=sheinbaum>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/preven-gasto-de-100-mdp-extra-para-combatir-coronavirus-en-cdmx-4974203.html Expenditure of 100 extra mp to prevent coronavirus in CDMX] {{in lang|es}} by Maleny Navarro, ''El Sol de M\u00e9xico'', March 15, 2020</ref> The first confirmed case of coronavirus in [[Acapulco]], Guerrero, was reported.<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/republica/sociedad/confirman-primer-caso-de-covid-19-en-guerrero-coronavirus-4974870.html Confirman primer caso de Covid-19 en Guerrero] {{in lang|es}} by Jos\u00e9 Francisco Zorroza, ''El Sol de Acapulco'', March 15, 2020</ref> [[Quer\u00e9taro]] reported two new cases, bringing the total to six.<ref>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/mundo/coronavirus-covid-19/nota/1932576/0/aumenta-seis-el-numero-de-casos-de-coronavirus-en-queretaro#info Queretaro increases the number of coronavirus cases to six] {{in lang|es}} by Francisco Floes Hernndez, El Universal, March 15, 2020</ref> [[Nuevo Leon]] reported its fifth case.<ref>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-suman-5-casos-positivos-en-nuevo-leon Coronavirus: 5 positive cases in Nuevo Leon] {{in lang|es}} by David Carrizales, March 15, 2020</ref> The [[Norte\u00f1o (music)|Norte\u00f1o]] group Los Tres Tristes Tigres released a [[corrido|song]] on March 15 titled \"El corrido del coronavirus\".<ref>[https://www.elsoldecuernavaca.com.mx/doble-via/virales/video-el-pin-coronavirus-a-todos-saco-de-quicio-el-nuevo-corrido-de-los-los-tres-tristes-tigres-covid19-covid-19-salud-humor-canciones-musica-nortea-comparas-de-panico-papel-de-bano-tom-hanks-amlo-disneyland-viral-corrido-4974778.html Los Tres Tristes Tigres compose \"El corrido del coronavirus\"] {{in lang|es}} by Miguel Ceballos, ''El Sol de Puebla'', March 15, 2020</ref>\n\n==== March 16 to 22====\n[[File:CoViD-19 MX.svg|thumb|upright=2|left|Number of cases (blue) and number of deaths (red) on a [[logarithmic scale]].]]\n\nAs of March 16, President L\u00f3pez Obrador continued to downplay the impact of coronavirus. \"Pandemics ... won't do anything to us,\" and accused the press and the opposition for its reportage.<ref>[https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2020-03-19/as-mexican-peso-collapses-over-coronavirus-threat-criticism-falls-on-president-lopez-obrador \"As Mexican peso collapses over coronavirus threat, criticism falls on president Lopez Obrador\" Los Angeles Times 2020/03/20] accessed March 20, 2020</ref>  On March 16, lawyer Marco Antonio del Toro petitioned the federal courts to cease all but essential activities for a period of 30 to 40 days because of the coronavirus outbreak.<ref>[https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/mexico/piden-suspender-actividades-en-juzgados-y-tribunales-por-coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-contagios-pandemia-epidemia-4976721.html Suspension of judicial activities for coronavirus requested] {{in lang|es}} Manrique Gandaria, ''El Sol de M\u00e9xico'', March 16, 2020</ref> The total of confirmed cases reached 82.<ref name=\"Marc 16 confirmed cases\">{{cite web |last1=Castillo Torres |first1=Gustavo |title=Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: 82 casos confirmados; s\u00f3lo 2% est\u00e1n graves |url=https://www.unotv.com/noticias/portal/nacional/detalle/coronavirus-mexico-82-casos-confirmados-solo-2-estan-graves-785052/ |website=UnoTV |date=March 17, 2020 |publisher=AMX Contenido S.A. de C.V. |accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref> The [[Universidad Aut\u00f3noma del Estado de Morelos|Autonomous University of the State of Morelos, (UAEM)]] suspended classes for its 22,000 students.<ref name=uaem>[https://www.milenio.com/estados/uaem-suspende-clases-por-coronavirus UAEM suspends classes due to coronavirus] {{in lang|es}} by David Monroy, ''Milenio'', March 16, 2020</ref> A diplomatic incident arose between the governments of Mexico and [[El Salvador]], concerning 12 Salvadorean citizens wearing face masks on a plane departing from Mexico City to San Salvador. [[Nayib Bukele]], president of El Salvador denounced as \"irresponsible\" that they were allowed to board the plane along with other passengers and offered to send a plane to transport them without contact with other people. The claim was supported by [[Avianca]] airline<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/AviancaCAM/status/1239696214469337088|title=Agradecemos al Presidente del El Salvador @nayibbukele por darnos la informaci\u00f3n y alertarnos sobre los pacientes con COVID-19 intentando abordar el vuelo de Avianca #431 proveniente de la Ciudad de M\u00e9xico hacia El Salvador el d\u00eda 16 de Marzo de 2020.|last=Centroam\u00e9rica|first=Avianca|date=March 16, 2020|website=@AviancaCAM|language=es|access-date=March 27, 2020}}</ref> while the Mexican government said that there were no reasons to assume that they were positive for COVID-19. Eventually, the flight was cancelled. [[Marcelo Ebrard]], head of Foreign Affairs announced after negative results of COVID tests of that Salvadorean passengers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.milenio.com/politica/coronavirus-llama-ebrard-nayib-bukele-aclarar-fuentes-pasajeros|title=Coronavirus: llama Ebrard a Nayib Bukele aclarar fuentes de pasajeros|website=milenio.com|access-date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn March 17, 11 new cases were confirmed, raising the national total to 93, with [[Campeche]] being the only state with no confirmed cases.<ref name=\"Confirmed cases 17 March\">{{cite web |last1=Milenio Digital |title=Secretar\u00eda de Salud reporta 93 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 206 sospechosos |url=https://www.milenio.com/politica/coronavirus-mexico-93-casos-confirmados-206-sospechosos |website=Milenio.com |publisher=Milenio Diario, S.A de C.V |accessdate=March 18, 2020}}</ref> Mexico's limited response, including allowing a large concert and the women's soccer championship, as well as a lack of testing, have been criticized. Critics note that president [[Andr\u00e9s Manuel L\u00f3pez Obrador|L\u00f3pez Obrador]] does not practice social distancing but continues to greet large crowds, and the borders have not been closed. Of particular concern is the health of thousands of migrants in temporary camps along the border with the United States. The former national commissioner for influenza in Mexico during the [[2009 flu pandemic]], Alejandro Mac\u00edas, said the problem is compounded by the fact that Mexico lacks sufficient intensive care unit beds, medical care workers and ventilators.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/mexico-government-pressure-coronavirus-response-200316210710906.html Mexico's government under pressure over coronavirus response] by Jihan Abdalla, Al Jazeera, March 17, 2020  [https://thehill.com/latino/488100-mexico-under-international-criticism-for-coronavirus-response Mexico under international criticism for coronavirus response] BY RAFAEL BERNAL, The Hill, March 18, 2020</ref>\n\nOn March 18, 25 more cases were confirmed raising the total to 118 cases and 314 suspected cases.<ref name=\"18march\">{{cite web |url=https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-mexico-casos-confirmados-positivos-covid19-hoy-miercoles-18-marzo-secretaria-salud/|title= Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: Hay 118 casos confirmados de COVID-19|date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.milenio.com/politica/coronavirus-mexico-118-casos-confirmados-314-sospechosos |title= Confirman 118 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 314 sospechosos |date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=Milenio}}</ref> Authorities in Jalisco are concerned about a group of 400 people who recently returned from [[Vail, Colorado]]; 40 people have symptoms of COVID-19.<ref>[https://www.milenio.com/internacional/coronavirus-mexico-18-marzo-noticias-hora-casos-vivo Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico, noticias de \u00faltima hora] Milenio, March 18, 2020</ref><ref>[https://www.latimes.com/world-nation/story/2020-03-20/some-of-mexicos-wealthiest-residents-went-to-colorado-to-ski-they-brought-home-coronavirus \"Some of Mexico's Wealthiest Residents Went to Colorado to Ski and Brought Home Coronavirus\". Los Angeles Times 2020/03/20] accessed March 20, 2020.</ref> The same day, the Mexican government announced that they will allocate 3.5 billion pesos ({{abbr|approx.|approximately}} 146 million US dollars{{refn|on March 18}}) to buy medical and laboratory equipment, washing and disinfection material, and ventilators.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-18-de-marzo-aumentan-118-los-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico |title= AUMENTAN A 118 LOS CASOS CONFIRMADOS DE CORONAVIRUS EN M\u00c9XICO |date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=El Universal}}</ref> During the night  the first COVID-19 related death in the country was confirmed, a 41-year-old man without a travel history outside the country who was hospitalized at the National Institute of Respiratory Diseases (INER).<ref name=\"death1\">{{cite web|url= https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/18/fallece-victima-de-covid-19-en-el-iner-9638.html |title= Fallece primera v\u00edctima de Covid-19 en el INER |date=March 18, 2020|language=es|work=[[La Jornada]]}}</ref> Colima Governor [[Jos\u00e9 Ignacio Peralta]] declared a state of emergency after the state's first case, a man who had recently returned from Germany, was reported on March 17.<ref>[https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Colima-declara-emergencia-por-COVID-19-20200318-0134.html Colima declara emergencia por COVID-19] El Informador, March 18, 2020</ref> [[Ford Motor Company|Ford]], [[Honda]], and [[Audi]] closed their manufacturing plants in Mexico.<ref name=ford>{{cite news|author=<!-- not stated -->|title=Empresas automotrices suspenden producci\u00f3n en M\u00e9xico|language=es |url=https://www.informador.mx/economia/Empresas-automotrices-suspenden-produccion-en-Mexico-20200318-0114.html|website=El Informador|date=March 18, 2020|access-date=March 19, 2020}}</ref> Hundreds of hotel employees in [[Canc\u00fan]] were fired.<ref name=cancun>[https://laverdadnoticias.com/quintanaroo/Coronavirus-Cancun-Comenzaron-los-despidos-en-los-hoteles-20200318-0006.html Coronavirus Canc\u00fan: Comenzaron los despidos en los hoteles] {{in lang|es}} by Angel Bal\u00e1n, La Verdad, March 18, 2020</ref>\n\nAuthorities announced on March 18 that they were looking for hundreds of citizens who may be carriers of the coronavirus, especially in the states of Puebla, Jalisco, Aguascalientes, and Guerrero. A four-member family in Puebla who had traveled to the United States kept their symptoms secret as they visited neighbors in La Vista and visited a gym. Authorities were still trying to track down the 400 people in Jalisco and Nayarit who recently traveled to Vail, Colorado. In Aguascalientes they were looking to track down passengers of Flight 2638 who traveled with a sick man from New York. The [[Autonomous University of Guerrero|Autonomous University of Guerrero (UAGRO)]] in Chilpancingo closed after a female student tested positive for the virus. The Technical Institute of Guerrero and the state Supreme Court also closed.<ref name=look>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexican-authorities-are-tracking-hundreds-possible-covid-19-carriers Mexican authorities are tracking hundreds of possible Covid 19 carriers] {{in lang|en}} by David Carrizales, March 19, 2020</ref>\n\n[[Morelos]] had its first two confirmed cases on March 19\u2014a 54-year-old woman from [[Cuautla, Morelos|Cuautla]] and a 37-year-old man from [[Cuernavaca]].<ref>[https://www.diariodemorelos.com/noticias/urgente-confirmados-ya-2-casos-de-coronavirus-en-morelos URGENTE: CONFIRMADOS YA 2 CASOS DE CORONAVIRUS COVID19 EN MORELOS] {{in lang|es}} ''Diario de Morelos'', March 19, 2020</ref> [[Sinaloa]] announced its third case, a 20-year-old woman from [[Culiac\u00e1n]].<ref>[https://www.debate.com.mx/culiacan/Confirman-el-tercer-caso-de-coronavirus-en-Sinaloa-20200319-0157.html Confirman el tercer caso de coronavirus en Sinaloa] {{in lang|es}} by FRANCISCO CASTRO, ''Debate'', March 19, 2020</ref>\n\nU.S Secretary of State [[Mike Pompeo]] announced on March 20 there would be restrictions on travel across the [[Mexico\u2013United States border]]. Said restrictions would not apply to cargo.<ref name=pompeo>{{cite web|website=Deadline|title=President Donald Trump Goes Off On NBC News Reporter, Comcast During Coronavirus Press Briefing|date=March 20, 2020|author=Ted Johnson|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/u-s-and-mexico-to-restrict-non-essential-travel-on-southern-border-mike-pompeo-warns-of-disinformation-1202888618/|language=en}}</ref> The [[Instituto Nacional de Antropolog\u00eda e Historia|National Institute of Anthropology and History (INAH)]] announced that the archaeological zones [[Teotihuac\u00e1n]], [[Xochicalco]], and [[El Tepozteco]] will be closed on March 21\u201322. [[Chich\u00e9n Itz\u00e1]] will close indefinitely starting March 21. [[Guachimontones]] will close 21, 22, and March 23. [[Palenque]], [[Tula (Mesoamerican site)|Tula]] and [[Tingambato]] will close March 21.<ref name=inah>[https://launion.com.mx/morelos/zona-sur/noticias/157226-cerraran-las-zonas-arqueologicas-de-xochicalco-y-tepoztlan.html?utm_medium=Social&utm_source=Facebook&fbclid=IwAR3J791dkyCGjqbxVpYJPQhZ2i6AJi6PvA9ylt65t0LS1hN20dxAET1jjoA#Echobox=1584718003 Cerrar\u00e1n las zonas arqueol\u00f3gicas de Xochicalco y Tepoztl\u00e1n] {{in lang|es}} La Union de Morelos, March 20, 2020</ref> [[Alsea (company)|Alsea]], which operates restaurants such as Starbucks, VIPS, and Domino's Pizza offered its employees unpaid leave.<ref name=alsea>[https://www.diariodemorelos.com/noticias/starbucks-y-vips-ofrecen-empleados-dejar-de-trabajar-un-mes-sin-goce-de-sueldo-por-covid-19?fbclid=IwAR1bHSJdt5O5D8QECH-3Yk547e2nKDlW-eZtwO870EFtZHBUAlkQOjOjr4s Starbucks y VIPs ofrecen a empleados dejar de trabajar un mes sin goce de sueldo, por COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} El Diario de Morelos, March 20, 2020</ref> Mayor Juanita Romero (PAN) of [[Nacozari de Garc\u00eda Municipality]], Sonora, declares a curfew, in effect until April 20. Only the [[President of Mexico]] has the legal authority to declare such a declaration.<ref name=curfew>[https://www.proceso.com.mx/622668/nacozari-toque-de-queda Alcaldesa de Nacozari ordena toque de queda, facultad exclusiva del presidente] {{in lang|es}} by Milton Martinez, Proceso, March 20, 2020</ref> During the night, 38 more cases and one more death were confirmed raising the total to 203 cases, 2 deaths, and 606 suspected cases.<ref name=\"20march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/seguridad/coronavirus-20-de-marzo-mexico-confirma-dos-muertos-por-covid-19-suma-203-casos |title= M\u00c9XICO CONFIRMA DOS MUERTOS POR CORONAVIRUS; SUMA 203 CASOS POSITIVOS |date=March 20, 2020|language=es|work=El Universal |author1= Alexis Ortiz |author2= Perla Miranda }}</ref>\n\nOn March 21 the total confirmed cases were 251.<ref name=\"21march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/sube-a-251-el-numero-de-contagiados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico/1371282 |title= Sube a 251 el n\u00famero de contagiados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |date=March 21, 2020|language=es|work=Exc\u00e9lsior |author1= Redacci\u00f3n}}</ref> One day later 65 more cases were confirmed and the total of suspected cases grew to 793.<ref name=\"22march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eleconomista.com.mx/politica/Cifra-de-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-Mexico-sube-a-316-Secretaria-de-Salud-20200322-0050.html |title= Con 316 casos confirmados, sigue fase de transici\u00f3n |date=March 22, 2020|language=es|work=El Economista |author1= Rolando Ramos}}</ref>\n\nOn March 22, bars, nightclubs, movie theaters, and museums were closed in Mexico City.<ref name=bars>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexico-city-closes-museums-bars-nightclubs-and-movie-theaters-bid-halt-coronavirus-spread Mexico City closes museums, bars, nightclubs, and movie theaters in a bid to halt coronavirus spread] {{in lang|en}} El Universal, March 23, 2020</ref> Governor [[Enrique Alfaro Ram\u00edrez]] of Jalisco announced that beginning Thursday, March 26, Jalisco and seven other states in the [[Baj\u00edo]] and western Mexico will block flights from areas such as [[COVID-19 pandemic in California|California]] that have a high rate of coronavirus. He also said that they will purchase 25,000 testing kits.<ref name=planes>[https://www.debate.com.mx/guadalajara/Jalisco-bloquearia-vuelos-y-compra-25-mil-pruebas-de-COVID-19-20200323-0224.html Jalisco will block flights and buy 25 thousand tests of COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} by CAROLINA SOL\u00cdS, Debate, March 23</ref>\n\n==== March 23 to 31====\n[[File:Acceso de personas con s\u00edntomas de enfermedades respiratorias al Instituto Nacional de Ciencias M\u00e9dicas y Nutrici\u00f3n Salvador Zubir\u00e1n.jpg|thumbnail|right|People entering a special respiratory illness symptom assessment area at the [[Salvador Zubir\u00e1n National Institute of Health Sciences and Nutrition|Instituto Nacional de Ciencias M\u00e9dicas y Nutrici\u00f3n Salvador Zubir\u00e1n]], Mexico City. The hospital was converted into a special care area for COVID patients.]]\n\nMexico entered Phase 2 of the coronavirus pandemic on March 23, according to the [[World Health Organization]], with 367 confirmed cases. Phase 2 includes cases where the sick individuals did not have direct contact with someone who had recently been in another country.<ref name=who>{{cite web |url= https://www.forbes.com.mx/noticias-salud-mexico-fase-2-pandemia-por-coronavirus-oms/ |title= M\u00e9xico, en Fase 2 de pandemia por Coronavirus: OMS |language=es |date= March 23, 2020 |website= Forbes M\u00e9xico}}</ref> On the same day it was confirmed that two more people died from COVID-19, raising the total to 4 reported deaths.<ref name=\"23march\">{{cite web |url= https://www.sdpnoticias.com/nacional/muertos-casos-confirmados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico-cifras-23-de-marzo.html |title= Suman 4 muertos por Covid-19 en M\u00e9xico; confirman 367 casos de contagio |date=March 23, 2020|language=es|work=SDP Noticias |author1= Alexis Pav\u00f3n}}</ref> That day was announced on President L\u00f3pez Obrador's daily press conference the realization of the National Campaign of Healthy Distancing ({{ill|Jornada Nacional de Sana Distancia|lt=|es||WD=}}) a national program of non-pharmaceutical measures based on [[social distancing]] among the behavioral changes suggested by WHO as hand washing, covering one's mouth when coughing, maintaining distance from other people, and monitoring and [[self-isolation]] for people who suspect they are infected.<ref name=social>{{cite web |url=https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/23/comienza-la-jornada-nacional-de-sana-distancia-1056.html|title=Comienza la Jornada Nacional de Sana Distancia|last=L|first=Ang\u00e9lica Enciso|date=March 23, 2020|work=[[La Jornada]]|language=es|access-date=March 27, 2020}}</ref> On that same day in the daily press conference was announced also a media campaign led by \"Susana Distancia\" (wordplay of a healthy distance) a fictional female [[superhero]] aiming to promote social distancing into the people.<ref name=susana>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dw.com/en/mexican-superhero-susana-distancia-swoops-in-to-promote-social-distancing/a-52873960|title=Mexican superhero Susana Distancia swoops in to promote social distancing|last=Martyr|first=Kate|work=[[Deutsche Welle]]|language=en-GB|date=March 21, 2020|access-date=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\nMeanwhile, a [[Warren Mitofsky|Mitofsky poll]] showed that 63% of Mexicans feared contracting Covid-19 and 25.5% feared dying from it. 28% said they were not willing to stay in their homes. 38.6% believed President L\u00f3pez Obrador was handling the situation well, and 37% disapproved.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/23/coronavirus-en-mexico-crece-el-descontento-con-el-gobierno-de-amlo-y-el-temor-al-contagio/ |title= Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: crece el descontento con el gobierno de AMLO y el temor al contagio |language=es |date= March 23, 2020 |website= Infobae}}</ref> Access to supermarkets in [[Coahuila]] was limited to one person per family, and the temperature of that person was taken before entering. The same rule applies to drugstores and convenience stores in the state, which has 12 confirmed cases of Covid-19.<ref name=supermarket>{{cite web |url= https://mvsnoticias.com/noticias/estados/solo-una-persona-por-familia-podra-acceder-a-supermercados-en-coahuila/ |title= Solo una persona por familia podr\u00e1 acceder a supermercados en Coahuila |author= Notimex  |language=es |date= March 23, 2020 |website= MVS Noticias}}</ref>\n\nAt his morning news conference on March 24, President [[Andr\u00e9s Manuel L\u00f3pez Obrador|L\u00f3pez Obrador]] announced that Mexico entered Phase 2 of the coronavirus pandemic, in effect until April 30. Gatherings of more than 100 people are prohibited, and both the army and the navy will participate. The armed forces have 1,738 doctors, 1,727 nurses, 100 intensive therapy ambulances, and 400 ambulances for transportation. The military also has 5 high specialty hospitals, 36 second-level hospitals, and 272 first-level hospitals with 262 health brigades across the country. Four deaths, 367 confirmed cases, and 826 suspected cases of COVID-19 have been reported.<ref name=amlo_phase2>{{cite web |url= https://www.unotv.com/noticias/portal/nacional/detalle/coronavirus-en-mexico-amlo-anuncia-plan-de-proteccion-contra-covid-19-776166/ |title= M\u00e9xico inicia fase 2 por coronavirus; toma estas medidas |author=  |language=es |date= March 24, 2020 |website= UNO TV}}</ref> The first Mexican woman died from COVID-19 on March 24, raising the total to 5 reported deaths in the country.<ref name=\"death5\">{{cite web|url= https://www.radioformula.com.mx/noticias/mexico/20200324/5-muertos-por-coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-martha-mujer-hospital-angeles-hoy/| title= Muere la primera mujer por Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; van 5 decesos|author=Diego Santiago|work=Grupo F\u00f3rmula|date= March 24, 2020}}</ref> On the same day 405 total cases of COVID-19 were confirmed.<ref name=\"24march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/suman-5-decesos-por-coronavirus-en-mexico-suben-a-405-los-casos-confirmados/|title= Suman 5 decesos por coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; suben a 405 los casos confirmados |author= Redacci\u00f3n |work=El Financiero|date= March 24, 2020|language=es}}</ref>\n\nOn March 25, Dr. Abelardo \u00c1vila, researcher at the [[Salvador Zubir\u00e1n National Institute of Health Sciences and Nutrition]] warned that Mexico was particularly vulnerable to the COVID-19 pandemic because of underlying chronic illnesses such as [[obesity]], [[diabetes]], and [[hypertension]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/25/mexico-es-mas-vulnerable-al-coronavirus-por-prevalencia-de-enfermedades-cronicas-dijeron-especialistas/ |title= M\u00e9xico es m\u00e1s vulnerable al coronavirus por prevalencia de enfermedades cr\u00f3nicas, dijeron especialistas |author=  |language=es |date= March 25, 2020 |website= Infobae}}</ref> Also on March 25 President L\u00f3pez Obrador ordered the [[Mexican Air Force]] to rescue Mexicans trapped in [[COVID-19 pandemic in Argentina|Argentina]].<ref name=airforce>[https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/25/lopez-obrador-ordeno-a-la-fuera-aerea-trasladar-a-su-pais-a-argentinos-varados-en-mexico-por-el-coronavirus-y-repatriar-a-connacionales/ L\u00f3pez Obrador orden\u00f3 a la Fuerza A\u00e9rea una misi\u00f3n de rescate de mexicanos y argentinos varados por coronavirus]{{in lang|es}} Infobae, March 25, 2020</ref> In Baja California, [[PROFECO]] closed two businesses in Tijuana for price-gouging.<ref name=profecobc>{{cite web |url= http://www.hiptex.com.mx/noticias/15232/clausura-profeco-dos-comercios-por-subir-precios-de-productos-basicos |title= Clausura Profeco dos comercios por subir precios de productos b\u00e1sicos |author=  |language=es |date= March 25, 2020 |website= Hiptex}}</ref> In Mexico City, Head of Government [[Claudia Sheinbaum]] announced financial support for families and micro industries affected by the pandemic. She also announced that automobile verification would be suspended through April 19. Movie theaters, bars, nightclubs, gyms, and other entertainment centers will remain closed.<ref name=finsupport>{{cite web |url= https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/25/creditos-para-micronegocios-y-500-pesos-para-ninos-las-acciones-de-cdmx-para-apoyar-a-la-poblacion-durante-emergencia-por-coronavirus/ |title= Cr\u00e9ditos para micronegocios y 500 pesos para ni\u00f1os: las acciones de CDMX para apoyar a la poblaci\u00f3n durante emergencia por coronavirus |author=  |language=es |date= March 25, 2020 |website= Infobae}}</ref> The same day it was reported that one man died from COVID-19 in [[San Luis Potos\u00ed]], raising the total to 6 reported deaths in Mexico and 475 confirmed cases.<ref name=\"death6\">{{cite web|author= Roc\u00edo L\u00f3pez |title= Muere hombre en San Luis Potos\u00ed por COVID-19; van 6 en M\u00e9xico|url= https://www.milenio.com/estados/coronavirus-san-luis-potosi-reportan-muerto-covid-19 |website=Milenio|date=March 25, 2020|language=es}}</ref><ref name=\"25march\">{{cite web|author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital |title= Van 6 muertes en M\u00e9xico por COVID-19; casos positivos ascienden a 475 |url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-mexico-muertes-covid19-casos-positivos-contagios-hoy-miercoles-25-marzo-2020-fase-dos-secretaria-salud/ |website=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico|date=March 25, 2020|language=es}}</ref> Governor [[Miguel Barbosa Huerta]] ([[National Regeneration Movement|Morena]]) claimed that only the wealthy were at risk, since the poor are immune to COVID-19.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/26/americas/mexico-coronavirus-luis-miguel-barbosa-intl/index.html |title= Mexican governor claims poor people are 'immune' from coronavirus |author1= Matt Rivers|author2= Natalie Gall\u00f3n |author3= CNN|language=en |date= March 26, 2020 |website= CNN}}</ref>\n\nOn March 26, President L\u00f3pez Obrador revealed he asked the [[G20]] to ensure that wealthy countries cannot take control of the world's medical supplies. He also called for assurances that borders would not be closed to commerce and that [[tariff]]s would not be unilaterally increased. Lastly, he called for an end to racism and discrimination.<ref name=g20>{{cite web |url= https://www.tvazteca.com/aztecanoticias/politica/notas/pide-amlo-en-g-20-que-onu-controle-comercio-de-medicamentos-de-covid-19 |title= Pide AMLO en G-20 que ONU controle comercio de medicamentos de COVID-19 |author= |language=es |date= March 26, 2020 |website= TV Azteca}}</ref> The Mexican government announced it would suspend most sectors' activities starting March 26 until April 19, with the exception of health and energy sectors, the oil industry; and public services such as water supply, waste management and public safety.<ref name=suspend_govt>{{cite news|last=Rueda |first=Rivelino|title=A partir de hoy para gobierno actividades|url=https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/a-partir-de-hoy-para-gobierno-actividades|work=El Financiero|date=March 26, 2020|access-date=March 26, 2020|language=es}}</ref> Protesters in [[Sonora]] insisted that the government limit border crossings with the United States.<ref name=border>{{cite web |url= https://news.yahoo.com/mexicans-demand-crackdown-americans-crossing-154146270.html |title= Coronavirus: Mexicans demand crackdown on Americans crossing the border |author= BBC |language=en |date= March 26, 2020 |website= Yahoo! News}}</ref> [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]] announced that \u201cin the next few days\u201d it will start to quarantine migrants who are returned to the [[Ciudad Ju\u00e1rez]] border crossing. About 65 migrants are deported from [[El Paso, Texas]] daily, about 5,200 this year.<ref name=chi>{{cite web |url= https://apnews.com/cf7b480e9e1dc84d1970665120302d9e |title= Mexican border city to quarantine returning migrants |author= |language=en |date= March 26, 2020 |website= AP}}</ref> Two more deaths were reported on this day; 585 cases were confirmed, and there were 2,156 suspected cases.<ref name=\"26march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.radioformula.com.mx/noticias/mexico/20200326/585-casos-coronavirus-en-mexico-salud-federal-hoy-ultimas-noticias-26-de-marzo/amp/ | title= Ya hay 585 casos confirmados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |author=Diego Santiago|work=Grupo F\u00f3rmula|date= March 26, 2020}}</ref> [[Human Rights Watch]] accused AMLO of endangering lives by not providing accurate information about the pandemic.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.hrw.org/news/2020/03/26/mexico-mexicans-need-accurate-covid-19-information |title= Mexico: Mexicans Need Accurate COVID-19 Information |author= |language=en |date= March 26, 2020 |website= Human Rights Watch}}</ref> The government of San Luis Potosi reported the death of a 57-year-old man on March 26, bringing the total number of deaths in the country to nine. He had hypertension and diabetes.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2020/03/27/tikitakas/1585280194_313276.html  |title= Coronavirus: San Luis confirma la segunda muerte en el estado |author= |language=es |date= March 26, 2020 |website= Mexico AS}}</ref> Citizens of [[Nogales, Sonora]] block border crossing from [[Nogales, Arizona]] in order to prevent the entrance of individuals with the virus infection and to prevent shortages of food, bottled water, toilet paper and cleaning supplies in local stores.<ref name=nogales>{{cite web |url= https://www.univision.com/noticias/america-latina/el-mundo-al-reves-mexicanos-bloquean-frontera-para-que-no-entren-a-su-pais-estadounidenses-contagiados-por-el-covid-19 |title= Mexicanos bloquean frontera para que no entren a su pa\u00eds estadounidenses contagiados por el COVID-19 |author= Isaias Alvarado |language=es |date= March 26, 2020 |website= Univision Noticias}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the Secretary of Health, a plurality of the 585 people infected in Mexico, 70, are between 30 and 34 years old. People over 65 are second, followed by those 25 to 29 and 45 to 49. The states with the most incidents are Mexico City (83), Jalisco (64) and Nuevo Leon (57).<ref>{{cite web |url= https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2020/03/27/tikitakas/1585334510_686136.html |title= De 30 a 34, la media de edad de contagios por coronavirus COVID-19 en M\u00e9xico |author= |language=es |date= March 27, 2020 |website= Mexico AS}}</ref>\n\nOn March 27 the federal government bought 5,000 ventilators from China as the government prepares for Phase 3 of the pandemic.<ref name=ventilator /> The total confirmed cases rose to 717; twelve deaths were reported, and there were 2,475 suspected cases.<ref name=\"27march\">{{cite web|url= https://politico.mx/minuta-politica/minuta-politica-gobierno-federal/ssa-presentar%C3%A1-informe-diario-sobre-coronavirus-en-m%C3%A9xico/ | title= Ssa: 717 casos confirmados de coronavirus y 2 mil 475 sospechosos |language=es |author=Pol\u00edtico MX|work=Pol\u00edtico.mx|date= March 27, 2020}}</ref> [[PROFECO]] (Office of the Federal Prosecutor for the Consumer) said it will fine merchants who unfairly raise the prices on household goods.<ref name=fine>{{cite web |url= https://www.adn40.mx/noticia/mexico/notas/2020-03-27-08-26/multa-de-hasta-3-millones-a-quien-suba-el-precio-de-la-canasta-basica |title= Multa de hasta 3 millones a quien suba el precio de la canasta b\u00e1sica |author= Redacci\u00f3n ADN40|language=es |date= March 27, 2020 |website= ADN40}}</ref> The governors of [[Governor of Nuevo Le\u00f3n|Nuevo Le\u00f3n]], [[Governor of Tamaulipas|Tamaulipas]] and [[Governor of Coahuila|Coahuila]] asked the federal government to close the border with [[COVID-19 pandemic in the United States|the United States]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.sinembargo.mx/27-03-2020/3756883 |title= Gobiernos de Coahuila, Nuevo Le\u00f3n y Tamaulipas piden a AMLO cerrar la frontera con EU por COVID-19 |author= Redacci\u00f3n/ Sin Embargo|language=es |date= March 27, 2020 |website= Sin Embargo}}</ref>\n\nOn March 28, Governor [[Omar Fayad]] of [[Hidalgo (state)|Hidalgo]] announced in a tweet that he tested positive for the virus and said that he was in self-quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/omar-fayad-gobernador-de-hidalgo-da-positivo-a-covid-19 | title= Omar Fayad, gobernador de Hidalgo, da positivo a COVID-19 |author=Redacci\u00f3n |work=El Financiero|language=es |date= March 28, 2020}}</ref> The [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Mexico]] said services should be held indoors with no more than twenty people present. They may cancel all [[Holy Week in Mexico|Holy Week]] celebrations if things do not improve.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.milenio.com/politica/arquidiocesis-celebracion-semana-santa-puerta-cerrada |title= Arquidi\u00f3cesis pide que celebraciones de Semana Santa sean a puerta cerrada |author= Elia Castillo|language=es |date= March 28, 2020 |website= Milenio}}</ref> In the evening the Secretariat of Health reported 131 new confirmed cases and four more deaths, raising the total to 848 confirmed cases and 16 deaths.<ref name=\"28march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/sube-a-848-los-contagiados-de-coronavirus-en-mexico/1372746 | title= Sube a 848 los contagiados de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |author=Redacci\u00f3n |work=Exc\u00e9lsior|language=es|date= March 28, 2020}}</ref> Governor [[Cuauht\u00e9moc Blanco]] of Morelos announced the seventh case and first death due to COVID-19 in the state, a 37-year-old man who had recently traveled to the United States.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.milenio.com/estados/coronavirus-confirman-el-primer-muerto-en-morelos-por-covid-19 |title= Cuauht\u00e9moc Blanco confirma la primer muerte por COVID-19 en Morelos |author= |language=es |date= March 28, 2020 |website= Milenio}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.diariodemorelos.com/noticias/situaci-n-actual-del-coronavirus-covid-19-en-morelos?fbclid=IwAR2mfAxLsQlJ6o3tndIvL0n8fOLVDzTE0pSZewHYL9ReOGBi6UznpBcmv4Y |title= SITUACI\u00d3N ACTUAL DEL CORONAVIRUS COVID-19 EN MORELOS |author= |language=es |date= March 28, 2020 |website= Diario de Morelos}}</ref> San Luis Potosi suspended wakes and funerals; the dead should be taken directly from the hospital to the [[crematorium]].<ref name=funeral>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-suspenden-funerales-por-covid-19-en-san-luis-potosi |title= Suspenden funerales por COVID-19 en San Luis Potos\u00ed |author= Redacci\u00f3n El Universal |language=es |date= March 28, 2020 |website= El Universal}}</ref>\n\nTabasco Governor [[Ad\u00e1n Augusto L\u00f3pez Hern\u00e1ndez]] tested positive for COVID-19 on March 29.<ref name=loppez_hernandez>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-gobernador-de-tabasco-da-positivo-covid-19-0 |title= Gobernador de Tabasco da positivo al Covid-19 |author=  |language=es |date= March 29, 2020 |website= El Universal}}</ref> Two tunnels with disinfectant spray were installed in the subways system of [[General Escobedo|Escobedo, Nuevo Le\u00f3n]].<ref>[https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/por-covid-19-colocan-tuneles-para-desinfectar-hasta-30-personas-por-minuto/1372842 Por Covid-19, colocan t\u00faneles para desinfectar hasta 30 personas por minuto] {{in lang|es}} by Aracely Garza, Excelsior, March 29, 2020</ref> The government of [[Yucat\u00e1n]] threatens fines of $86,000 pesos and up to three years in prison for individuals who have tested positive for coronavirus and do not self-quarantine.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://noticieros.televisa.com/ultimas-noticias/coronavirus-multas-86-mil-pesos-personas-enfermas-aislen-yucatan/ |title= Multas de 86 mil pesos a personas con coronavirus que no se a\u00edslen en Yucat\u00e1n |author=  |language=es |date= March 29, 2020 |website= Noticieros Televisa}}</ref> The state of [[Quer\u00e9taro]] registered its first death from COVID-19, a 56-year-old man.<ref name=gov_tabasco>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/estados/coronavirus-queretaro-registra-la-primera-muerte-por-covid-19 Quer\u00e9taro registra la primera muerte por COVID-19] {{in lang|es}} El Universal, March 29, 2020</ref> The same day 993 cases of COVID-19 and 20 deaths from the disease were confirmed.<ref name=\"29march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.publimetro.com.mx/mx/coronavirus-covid-19/2020/03/29/casos-muertes-coronavirus-mexico-29-marzo-2020.html | title= Suman 993 casos de coronavirus en M\u00e9xico; hay 20 muertos|author=Publimetro |work=Publimetro|language=es|date= March 29, 2020}}</ref> Between 27 and March 29, 566 Mexicans were brought home from other countries: 62 from [[COVID-19 pandemic in Colombia|Colombia]], 53 from [[COVID-19 pandemic in Ecuador|Ecuador]], 299 from [[COVID-19 pandemic in Peru|Peru]], 28 from [[COVID-19 pandemic in Guatemala|Guatemala (via land)]], and 134 from [[COVID-19 pandemic in Cuba|Cuba]]. In turn, the Mexican government helped 86 people return to Ecuador, 99 to Peru, and 49 to Cuba.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/03/29/en-dos-dias-fueron-repatriados-576-mexicanos-suman-mas-de-8-mil-8945.html |title= En dos d\u00edas, fueron repatriados 576 mexicanos; suman m\u00e1s de 8 mil |author=La Redacci\u00f3n  |language=es |date= March 29, 2020 |website= La Jornada}}</ref>\n\nOn March 30, the total number of cases of COVID-19 surpassed one thousand with 1,094 confirmed cases and 28 reported deaths in the country. In the evening, a national health emergency was declared by Secretary [[Marcelo Ebrard]]; all sectors in the country are urged to stop most of their activities.<ref name=\"30march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/sociedad/coronavirus-30-de-marzo-mexico-supera-los-mil-contagios-de-coronavirus-suman-mil-94 | title= M\u00c9XICO, EN EMERGENCIA SANITARIA; SUPERA LOS MIL CASOS DE CORONAVIRUS |author=Redacci\u00f3n  |work=El Universal|language=es|date= March 30, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn the early morning of March 31, 50,000 test kits, 100,000 masks and five ventilators (donated by [[Jack Ma]] and the [[Alibaba Group|Alibaba]] Foundation of China) arrived at the [[Mexico City International Airport]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://aristeguinoticias.com/0104/mexico/llegan-a-mexico-50-mil-kits-de-pruebas-para-detectar-covid-19-donados-por-china/ |title= Llegan a M\u00e9xico 50 mil kits de pruebas para detectar Covid-19, donados por China |author= |language=es |date= March 31, 2020 |website= Aristegui Noticias}}</ref> Nurses in Jalisco have been forced to get off public transportation and physically attacked by people fearful of COVID-19. Medical workers there and elsewhere have been advised not to wear their uniforms outside the hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/03/31/bajan-del-transporte-a-enfermeras-en-jalisco-y-les-rocian-cloro-por-miedo-a-contagios-de-covid-19/ |title= Bajan del transporte a enfermeras en Jalisco y les roc\u00edan cloro por miedo a contagios de Covid-19 |author= |language=es |date= March 31, 2020 |website= Infobae}}</ref> The same day the total confirmed cases of COVID-19 reached 1215 and one more death was reported. The government of [[Mexico City]] announced that 90% of the businesses in Mexico City would have to close because of the national health emergency declaration of the day before.<ref name=\"31march\">{{cite web|url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-31-de-marzo-casos-de-covid-19-en-mexico-llegan-mil-215-hay-29-muertos | title= CASOS DE CORONAVIRUS EN M\u00c9XICO LLEGAN A MIL 215; HAY 29 MUERTOS |author=Redacci\u00f3n  |work=El Universal|language=es|date= March 31, 2020}}</ref> In [[Austin, Texas]], Public Health officials started investigating an apparent cluster of COVID-19 after 28 of 70 \u201cspring breakers\u201d (students at the [[University of Texas at Austin]]) tested positive following their trip to [[Cabo San Lucas]], [[Baja California Sur]], in early March.<ref>{{cite web|website=[[KXAN-TV]]|date=March 31, 2020|title=28 of 70 spring breakers on Mexico trip test positive for coronavirus |url=https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/KXAN-TV}}</ref> The [[Mexican Social Security Institute|Mexican Social Security Institute (IMSS)]] in [[Monclova]], Coahuila, reported that 29 medical and nursing staff tested positive for COVID-19. No patients have been infected.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-mexico/coronavirus-infects-29-medical-workers-at-mexico-hospital-idUSKBN21J3W2 |title= Coronavirus infects 29 medical workers at Mexico hospital |author= |language=en |date= March 31, 2020 |website= Reuters}}</ref>\n\n=== April 2020 ===\n\n==== April 1 to 15 ====\n[[File: Monterrey airport covid19.jpg |thumbnail|right|People wearing face masks at the [[Monterrey International Airport]] due to the COVID-19 pandemic.]]\nIt was reported on April 1 that seven migrants from Puebla residing in [[COVID-19 pandemic in New York (state)|New York]] have died of COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.animalpolitico.com/2020/04/siete-migrantes-poblanos-muertos-nueva-york-covid-19/ |title= Suman siete migrantes poblanos muertos en Nueva York por COVID-19 |author= |language=es |date= April 1, 2020 |website= Animal Pol\u00edtico}}</ref> Authorities reported 46% of cases as recoveries, which represents approximately 634 recoveries.<ref name=\"youtube1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=urlavWn2FWw&feature=youtu.be&t=675 |title=#ConferenciaDePrensa: #Coronavirus #COVID19 #Qu\u00e9dateEnCasaYa &#124; 1\u00b0 de abril de 2020 |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=April 2, 2020}}</ref> In Coahuila, 21  health workers contracted the virus and one doctor died from it, bringing the number of deaths among doctors employed by IMSS to four. Nineteen of the 21 cases in Coahuila are mild and the individuals are ambulatory.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/several-health-workers-have-contracted-covid-19-mexico |title= Several health workers have contracted COVID-19 in Mexico |author= |language=en |date= April 1, 2020 |website= El Universal English}}</ref> Later the same day, 1,378 cases and 37 deaths of COVID-19 were reported in Mexico.<ref name=\"1april\">{{cite web|url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-resumen-miercoles-1-abril-2020-secretaria-salud-muertos-contagiados-cifras/ | title= Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: Resumen mi\u00e9rcoles 1 de abril 2020 |author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |work=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico|language=es|date= April 1, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 2, 1,510 cases of COVID-19 and 13 more deaths related to the disease were confirmed by Mexican authorities.<ref name=\"2april\">{{cite web|url= https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/nacional/llega-a-50-la-cifra-de-muertos-por-coronavirus-y-van-mil-510-casos-confirmados | title= Llega a 50 la cifra de muertos por coronavirus en M\u00e9xico y van mil 510 casos confirmados |author=Redacci\u00f3n  |work=El Financiero|language=es|date= April 2, 2020}}</ref> In Mexico City, as hotels are forced to close, hotel guests are evicted from their rooms.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.elsoldemexico.com.mx/metropoli/cdmx/a-la-calle-hoteles-de-la-cdmx-desalojan-a-huespedes-ante-cuarentena-pandemia-covid-19-coronavirus-5052588.html |title= \u00a1A la calle! Hoteles de la CDMX desalojan a hu\u00e9spedes ante Covid-19 |author= Eduardo Torres |language=es |date= April 2, 2020 |website= El Sol de M\u00e9xico}}</ref>\n\nOn April 3, 1,688 cases and 60 deaths were confirmed by the Secretariat of Health.<ref name=\"3april\">{{cite web|url= https://politica.expansion.mx/mexico/2020/04/03/los-casos-positivos-de-coronavirus-se-elevan-a-1-688-y-a-60-los-decesos| title= Los casos positivos de coronavirus se elevan a 1,688 y a 60 los decesos|author=Expansi\u00f3n Pol\u00edtica  |work=Expansi\u00f3n Pol\u00edtica|language=es|date= April 3, 2020}}</ref> The following day, 202 more cases and 19 more deaths were confirmed by Mexican authorities.<ref name=\"4april\">{{cite web|url= https://www.dineroenimagen.com/actualidad/aumenta-1890-el-numero-de-contagiados-por-coronavirus-en-mexico/121274 | title= Aumenta a 1,890 el n\u00famero de contagiados por coronavirus en M\u00e9xico |author= |work=Dinero en Imagen |language=es|date= April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 5, President L\u00f3pez Obrador presented his plan to reactivate the economy. He said he did not want to increase fuel prices or taxes, and he was looking to hire more medical professionals for the armed forces. He said there was sufficient money to build the proposed thermoelectric plants that are needed in Yucat\u00e1n, Baja California and elsewhere. He stated that he had support from the private sector and he expressed his confidence that Mexico would soon overcome the current crisis.<ref name=plan>{{cite web|website=Mexico AS|title=AMLO presenta sus medidas para reactivar econom\u00eda ante el COVID-19 |language=es|trans-title=AMLO presents his measures to revive the economy effected by COVID-19|date=April 5, 2020 |author=Uriel Salmeron |url=https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2020/04/06/tikitakas/1586130668_050121.html}}</ref> On the same day , the total number of cases surpassed two thousand with 2143 cases and 94 deaths.<ref name=\"5april\">{{cite web|url= https://noticieros.televisa.com/ultimas-noticias/coronavirus-conferencia-mexico-hoy-5-abril-2020/ | title= Suman 94 muertos en M\u00e9xico por coronavirus; hay 2 mil 143 casos |author= Noticieros Televisa |work=Noticieros Televisa |language=es|date= April 5, 2020}}</ref>\n\nPresident L\u00f3pez Obrador and Governor Blanco of Morelos dedicated the ISSSTE hospital \u201cCarlos Calero\u201d in Cuernavaca that was going to be set aside to care for patients with COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|website=Mexico AS|title=Cuauht\u00e9moc Blanco y AMLO pusieron ejemplo de la 'sana distancia' |language=es|trans-title=Cuauht\u00e9moc Blanco and AMLO set an example of \u2018social distancing\u2019|date=April 5, 2020 |author=Erick de la Rosa |url=https://mexico.as.com/mexico/2020/04/05/tikitakas/1586047733_148789.html}}</ref> Fifteen new deaths were registered on April 5, bringing the total to 94. The age range of the deceased was from 26 to 91 years old with a median age of 56.5. Of the 94 dead, 79% were males and 21% were females.<ref>{{cite web |website=Mexico AS|title=Muertos por Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico hoy, 5 de abril|language=es|trans-title=Deaths by Coronavirus in Mexico today, April 5|date=April 5, 2020 |author=Juan Carlos Navarro |url=https://mexico.as.com/autor/juan_carlos_navarro_hernandez/a/}}</ref>\n\nOn April 6, 2,439 cases were confirmed and the total number of deaths surpassed one hundred with 125 deaths reported.<ref name=\"6april\">{{cite web|url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/muertos-mexico-covid-19-casos-confirmados-coronavirus-corte-secretaria-salud-lunes-6-abril-2020/ | title= COVID-19 en M\u00e9xico: Ssa reporta 125 muertos y dos mil 439 casos confirmados |author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |work=El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |language=es|date= April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe [[List of diplomatic missions of Mexico|Mexican Consulate]] in [[Shanghai]], China, announced on April 7 that the [[Aerom\u00e9xico]] ''Misionero de Paz,'' a [[Boeing 787 Dreamliner|Boeing 787-8]] filled with emergency medical supplies was en route to Mexico.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://mty.telediario.mx/nacional/avion-con-suministros-medicos-por-covid-19-se-dirige-mexico-desde-china |title= Avi\u00f3n con suministros m\u00e9dicos por covid-19 se dirige a M\u00e9xico desde China |author= Milenio Digital |date= April 7, 2020 |language=es |website= Telediario}}</ref> That same day, 2785 cases and 141 deaths related to COVID-19 were confirmed.<ref name=\"7april\" >{{cite web |url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/coronavirus-covid-19-mexico-resumen-muertos-contagiados-secretaria-salud-martes-7-abril-2020/ |title= Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: Resumen martes 7 de abril 2020 |author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |date= April 7, 2020 |language=es |website= El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico}}</ref>\n\nOn April 8, twenty medical and nursing schools withdrew their students from social service in hospitals due to the lack of adequate protection.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.jornada.com.mx/ultimas/politica/2020/04/08/anuies-se-une-al-ipn-y-a-unam-y-retira-sus-estudiantes-de-hospitales-7806.html |title= Veintena de universidades tambi\u00e9n retira estudiantes de hospitales |author= Jos\u00e9 Antonio Rom\u00e1n |date= April 8, 2020 |language=es |website= La Jornada}}</ref> [[Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell Ram\u00edrez]], head of the Undersecretariat of Prevention and Health Promotion at the Mexican Secretariat of Health, estimated there were unconfirmed 26,519 cases of COVID-19 in the country.<ref name=\"sentinela\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexicos-health-ministry-estimates-there-are-26000-covid-19-cases-country |title= Mexico's Health Ministry estimates there are 26,000 COVID-19 cases in the country|author= Teresa Moreno |date= April 8, 2020 |language=en |website= El Universal}}</ref> In the evening it was announced that Mexico surpassed the three thousand confirmed cases with 3,181 cases and 174 deaths.<ref name=\"8april\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-8-de-abril-mexico-ya-supera-los-3-mil-contagios-de-covid-19-contabiliza-174 |title= M\u00c9XICO YA SUPERA LOS 3 MIL CONTAGIOS DE CORONAVIRUS; CONTABILIZA 174 MUERTOS |author= Redacci\u00f3n |date= April 8, 2020 |language=es |website= El Universal}}</ref> The following day, 260 more cases and 20 more deaths were reported by Mexican authorities.<ref name=\"9april\">{{cite web |url= https://heraldodemexico.com.mx/pais/muertos-mexico-covid19-casos-confirmados-coronavirus-reporte-secretaria-de-salud-jueves-9-abril-2020/ |title= COVID-19 M\u00e9xico: SSa reporta 194 muertos y tres mil 441 casos confirmados |author= Redacci\u00f3n Digital El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico |date= April 9, 2020 |language=es |website= El Heraldo de M\u00e9xico}}</ref> Jos\u00e9 Ignacio Precaido Santos of the General Health Council announced that at least 146 private hospitals will make beds available to treat COVID-19 patients on a non-profit basis.<ref name=beds>[https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexican-government-will-use-private-hospitals-treat-covid-19-patients Mexican government will use private hospitals to treat COVID-19 patients] El Universal {{in lang|en}}, April 8, 2020</ref>\n\nTwo pregnant women are among the 119 deaths reported as of April 9. These are the first two cases of pregnant women in Mexico to die from COVID-19; both had problems with [[obesity]] and [[Diabetes and pregnancy|diabetes]].<ref>{{cite web |title=First deaths of pregnant women from COVID-19 reported in Mexico |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/first-deaths-pregnant-women-covid-19-reported-mexico |website=El Universal |accessdate=April 18, 2020 |language=en |date=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 10, the total confirmed deaths surpassed two hundred with 233 deaths and 3,844 cases confirmed by Mexican authorities.<ref name=\"10april\">{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-10-de-abril-mexico-supera-los-200-muertos-por-covid-19-llega-3-mil-844-contagios |title= M\u00c9XICO SUPERA LOS 200 MUERTOS POR COVID-19; LLEGA A 3 MIL 844 CONTAGIOS |author= Redacci\u00f3n |date= April 10, 2020 |language=es |website= El Universal}}</ref> The government of [[Baja California]] closed a plant belonging to the multinational giant [[Smiths Group]] after the firm refused to sell [[ventilator]]s to the Mexican government.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://apnews.com/685d5779e5a3607bcc56ac79b168701c |title= Mexico closes US owned plant for refusal to sell ventilators |author= |date= April 10, 2020 |language=en |website= AP}}</ref> On the same day, [[List of diplomatic missions of Mexico|Mexican consulates in the United States]] announced the deaths of 181 Mexican nationals due to the COVID-19 pandemic. One hundred forty-nine of those cases were in [[COVID-19 pandemic in New York (state)|New York]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/covid-19-dozens-mexicans-have-died-us-coronavirus |title= COVID-19: dozens of Mexicans have died in the U.S. from coronavirus |author= |date= April 11, 2020 |language=en |website= El Universal}}</ref> The national network of women shelters reports a 60% increase in calls for help since the coronavirus pandemic began.<ref>{{cite web |title=Domestic abuse spikes in Mexico amid virus outbreak |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/domestic-abuse-spikes-mexico-virus-outbreak-200410143527001.html |website=www.aljazeera.com |accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 11, 375 more cases and 40 more deaths were confirmed.<ref name=\"11april\">{{cite web |url=https://www.elfinanciero.com.mx/salud/casos-confirmados-de-covid-19-suben-a-4-219-se-registran-273-muertes |title= CASOS CONFIRMADOS DE COVID-19 SUBEN A 4,219; SE REGISTRAN 273 MUERTES |author= Redacci\u00f3n |date= April 11, 2020 |language=es |website= El Financiero}}</ref> Nineteen Mexican agricultural workers in [[Kelowna]], British Columbia, Canada, have contracted the disease but none are reported as serious.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/19-mexican-agricultural-workers-have-contracted-covid-19-canada |title= 19 Mexican agricultural workers have contracted COVID-19 in Canada |author= |date= April 11, 2020 |language=en |website= El Universal}}</ref>\n\nOn April 12, the government established the \"National Contingency Center\" (CNC) to fight COVID-19. It will be led by the military and will have scientists and health technicians advising about steps to combat the pandemic.<ref name=cnc>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexico-creates-national-contingency-center-fight-covid-19-pandemic |title= Mexico creates the National Contingency Center to fight the COVID-19 pandemic |author= |date= April 12, 2020 |language=en |website= El Universal}}</ref>\n\nOn April 13, the number of COVID-19 infections in the country passed 5,000; there were 332 deaths.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/coronavirus-13-de-abril-mexico-supera-los-5-mil-casos-de-covid-19-llega-332-muertos |title= M\u00e9xico supera los 5 mil casos de covid-19, llega 332 muertos |author= |date= April 13, 2020 |language=es |website= El Universal}}</ref> The [[Mexican Navy]] announced it would open ten voluntary self-isolation units to shelter 4,000 COVID-19 victims in Mexico City, Guerrero, Jalisco, Michoacan, Sinaloa, Tamaulipas and Veracruz.<ref name=voluntary>{{cite web |url= https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexico-will-open-10-voluntary-isolation-centers-amid-covid-19-pandemic |title= Mexico will open 10 voluntary isolation centers amid the COVID-19 pandemic |author= |date= April 13, 2020 |language=en |website= El Universal}}</ref> Sonora became the first state in the country to declare a curfrew.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/04/14/coronavirus-en-mexico-sonora-es-el-primer-estado-en-decretar-el-confinamiento-obligatorio-con-sanciones/|title=Coronavirus in Mexico: Sonora is the first state to decree mandatory confinement with sanctions|last=|first=|date=|website=Infobae|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nOn April 14, Governor [[Antonio Echevarr\u00eda Garc\u00eda]] of Nayarit said he wanted to close the state's borders to visitors from Jalisco and Sinaloa, noting that young, apparently healthy people from other areas have visited their elderly relatives in the state. ''Y son las personas que han fallecido y estas personas que vienen del otro lado traen el virus, no presentan ning\u00fan s\u00edntoma y hacen la contaminadera,'' (\"And they are the people who have died and these people who come from the other side bring the virus, do not present any symptoms and cause the contamination\") said Echevarr\u00eda.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Nayarit-busca-cerrar-fronteras-con-Jalisco-y-Sinaloa-20200414-0108.html |title= Nayarit busca cerrar fronteras con Jalisco y Sinaloa |author=SUN |date= April 14, 2020 |language=es |website= El Informador}}</ref> Oaxaca Governor [[Alejandro Murat Hinojosa]] reported the theft of more than 20 kits of medical supplies used for treatment of COVID-19 were stolen from the Aurelio Valdivieso General Hospital. A week earlier, seven ventilators had been stolen from the IMSS hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/coronavirus/covid-19-treatment-equipment-stolen-in-oaxaca/ |title= Ventilators, other Covid-19 treatment equipment stolen in Oaxaca |author= |date= April 14, 2020 |language=es |website= Mexico News Daily}}</ref> Baja California Governor [[Jaime Bonilla Valdez]] said that doctors in Tijuana are \u201cfalling like flies\u201d as 21 medical workers at IMSS clinic #20 have been diagnosed with COVID-19 and 15 others are suspected of having it; one doctor at the IMSS general hospital has been infected and six have suspected cases.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/coronavirus/doctors-are-falling-like-flies-in-tijuana/ |title= Doctors are 'falling like flies' in Tijuana, Baja California governor warns |author= |date= April 14, 2020 |language=es |website= Mexico News Daily}}</ref>\n\nAn April 15 report by ''Quinto Elemento Lab'' showed that 30% of Mexicans cannot get local information about COVID-19 infections. [[Mexico City]] does not break down statistics for its 16 boroughs, and the [[State of Mexico]], [[Quer\u00e9taro]], [[Tlaxcala]], and [[Yucat\u00e1n]] do not reveal information on the municipal level. Governments said revealing the information would violate patients' privacy.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/coronavirus/local-level-stats-showing-covid-19-infection-are-secret/ |title= In 4 states and CDMX, local-level stats showing Covid-19 infection are secret |author= |date= April 15, 2020 |language=es |website= Mexico News Daily}}</ref> The [[National Guard (Mexico)|National Guard]] began providing security support for hospitals run by the IMSS in nineteen states on April 15.<ref>{{cite web |title=COVID-19: Mexico's National Guard steps in to protect IMSS hospitals |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/covid-19-mexicos-national-guard-steps-protect-imss-hospitals |website=El Universal |accessdate=April 18, 2020 |language=en |date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==== April 16 to 30 ====\n[[File:A clothing shop Tijuana's Plaza Rio shopping mall closed due to COVID-19..jpg|thumb|A [[Clothes shop|clothes store]] in [[Plaza R\u00edo Tijuana]] closed due to COVID-19.]]\n\nThe first death attributed to COVID-19 of a minor under 25 is reported in [[Tabasco]] on April 16, a two-year-old girl with [[Down syndrome]] and [[Congenital heart defect|congenital heart disease]].<ref>{{cite web |title=First COVID-19 death of minor registered in Mexico |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/first-covid-19-death-minor-registered-mexico |website=El Universal |accessdate=April 18, 2020 |language=en |date=April 16, 2020}}</ref> The government announced on April 16 that it will restrict transportation between areas of the country that are infected with COVID-19 (mostly large cities) and areas that are not infected, without specifying what areas are included or how it will be enforced.<ref name=travel>{{cite news|url= https://apnews.com/9e5bb61c8bb22aba3fe0557aa82f592e | title= Mexico to restrict mobility to areas less affected by virus |agency= Associated Press|work=AP|language=en|date= April 16, 2020}}</ref> President L\u00f3pez Obrador also said that based upon current projections, the 979 municipalities that have not had reported cases of coronavirus will be able to reopen schools and workplaces on 17 May; the date is June 1 for the 463 municipalities that have. The elderly and other vulnerable groups will still be requested to stay home, and physical distancing should remain in place until 30 May. It is expected that the pandemic will end in the metropolitan area on June 25.<ref name=reopen>{{cite web |title=COVID-19: Mexicans will return to work and school between May 17 and June 1 |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/covid-19-mexicans-will-return-work-and-school-between-may-17-and-june-1 |website=El Universal |accessdate=April 18, 2020 |language=en |date=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[TV Azteca]] called for the public to ignore information and warnings from [[Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell Ram\u00edrez]] on April 17: \"Like every night, the Undersecretary of Health, Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell led the conference on COVID-19 in Mexico. But his numbers and conferences have already become irrelevant. Moreover, we tell him with all his words, no longer pay attention to Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Tourliere |first1=Mathieu |title=TV Azteca llama a ya no hacerle caso a L\u00f3pez-Gatell |url=https://www.proceso.com.mx/626362/tv-azteca-llama-a-ya-no-hacerle-caso-a-lopez-gatell?fbclid=IwAR0dmgzfLY3P8LjekSLDrrphhVS7v9YqtSLn7nJOA4BZ_FIj4OsjHrEBcXU |website=Proceso portal de noticias |accessdate=April 18, 2020 |language=es-MX |date=April 18, 2020|trans-title=TV Azteca calls to no longer pay attention to L\u00f3pez-Gatell|quote=Como todas las noches, el subsecretario de Salud, Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell encabez\u00f3 la conferencia sobre el covid-19 en M\u00e9xico. Pero sus cifras y sus conferencias ya se volvieron irrelevantes. Es m\u00e1s, se lo decimos con todas sus palabras, ya no le haga caso a Hugo L\u00f3pez-Gatell}}</ref> President L\u00f3pez Obrador\u2032s proposal for a [[United Nations General Assembly]] resolution to prevent price gouging or hoarding of medical supplies by wealthy countries has 161 co-sponsors. The proposal was first made during a video conference of the G20.<ref>{{cite web |title=Apoyan 161 pa\u00edses PROPUESTA de M\u00c9XICO ante la ONU para EVITAR ACAPARAMIENTO de insumos contra el Covid-19 |url=https://www.sdpnoticias.com/internacional/propuesta-mexico-onu-insumos-contra-covid-19-amlo-juan-ramon-de-la-fuente.html?fbclid=IwAR3v9kiclsYKdw3qscD66glz1LmxIiq25vf2sauvNSst6qAx1nJEQtffAGg |website=SDPnoticias.com |accessdate=April 18, 2020 |language=spanish|trans-title=Mexico's proposal receives majority support among UN members}}</ref> [[Pemex]] reports 10 deaths, 92 cases, and 1,052 suspected cases of COVID-19. 17 have recovered.<ref>{{cite web |title=Pemex registers COVID-19 cases among its workers and beneficiaries |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/pemex-registers-covid-19-cases-among-its-workers-and-beneficiaries-0 |website=El Universal |accessdate=April 18, 2020 |language=en |date=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 18, Alonso P\u00e9rez Rico, Health Secretary for Baja California, reported that at least 30 doctors in the state, principally in [[Mexicali Municipality|Mexicali]], have tested positive for COVID-19. None is critical.<ref>{{cite web |title=Reportan a 30 m\u00e9dicos con COVID-19 en BC |url=https://www.debate.com.mx/estados/Reportan-a-30-medicos-con-Covid-19-en-BC--20200417-0324.html |website=EL DEBATE |language=es-ES|trans-title=30 doctors in BC reported with COVID-19}}</ref>\n\nOn April 20 the [[Secretariat of National Defense (Mexico)|Secretariat of National Defense (Sedena)]] announced that it had hired 3,158 of the 4,572 health professionals it needs.<ref>{{cite web |title=La Sedena ha contratado tres mil 158 m\u00e9dicos y enfermeras por coronavirus |url=https://www.informador.mx/mexico/La-Sedena-ha-contratado-tres-mil-158-medicos-y-enfermeras-por-coronavirus-20200421-0094.html |website=El Informador :: Noticias de Jalisco, M\u00e9xico, Deportes & Entretenimiento |accessdate=April 21, 2020 |language=es-ES|trans-title=Sedena has hired 3,158 doctors and nurses for coronavirus}}</ref> A Venezuelan YouTuber residing in Mexico City broke quarantine after being diagnosed with COVID-19 on April 20. Authorities had to sanitize the grocery store he contaminated and his immigration status was being investigated. His girlfriend similarly broke quarantine a few days earlier.<ref>{{cite web |title=Venezuelan youtuber diagnosed with COVID-19 sparks outrage after he ignored isolation measures in Mexico City |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/venezuelan-youtuber-diagnosed-covid-19-sparks-outrage-after-he-ignored-isolation-measures |website=El Universal {{in lang|en}} |accessdate=April 21, 2020 |language=en |date=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n\nMexico entered Phase 3 of its contingency plan on April 21. 712 deaths and 8,772 confirmed cases were reported.<ref name=phase3>{{cite web |title=Mexico enters Phase 3 of its contingency plan to fight COVID-19 |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/english/mexico-enters-phase-3-its-contingency-plan-fight-covid-19 |website=El Universal {{in lang|en}} |accessdate=April 21, 2020 |language=en |date=April 21, 2020}}</ref> The Mexico City General Hospital delivered the wrong body to the widow of \u00c1ngel Dorado Salinas, 52. She discovered the mistake when she saw a photograph of the corpse.<ref>{{cite web |title=Hospital delivers wrong body to widow of presumed virus victim |url=https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/coronavirus/hospital-delivers-wrong-body-to-widow-of-presumed-virus-victim/ |website=Mexico News Daily |accessdate=April 24, 2020 |date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\nRecently{{When|date=April 2020}} it has come to media attention that the Mexican drug cartels, in an effort to boost their own popularity and in response to poor efforts by the Mexican presidency, have been distributing supplies to impoverished citizens in the street.<ref>{{cite web|author=Haven Orecchio-Egresitz |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/mexican-cartels-are-giving-out-coronavirus-aid-to-elderly-residents-2020-4 |title=Mexican cartels are giving out coronavirus aid to elderly residents |publisher=Business Insider |date=April 13, 2020 |accessdate=April 24, 2020}}</ref> The president of Mexico has since called on the cartels to stop distributing supplies and \u201cend violence\u201d instead.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/mexico-president-tells-gangs-stop-handing-coronavirus-aid-200421060420772.html |title=Mexico president tells gangs to stop handing out coronavirus aid &#124; Mexico News |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=April 16, 2020 |accessdate=April 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe number of coronavirus cases surges past 10,000 to 10,544 with 970 deaths on April 21.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: son 970 muertes y 10,544 casos confirmados |url=https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/04/23/coronavirus-en-mexico-son-970-muertes-y-10544-casos-confirmados/ |website=Infobae |accessdate=April 23, 2020 |language=es-ES|trans-title=Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: son 970 muertes y 10,544 casos confirmados}}</ref>\n\nSix people were arrested in [[Tlaquepaque|San Pedro Tlaquepaque]] and [[Tlajomulco de Z\u00fa\u00f1iga]], Jalisco, for violating the state's quarantine orders on April 22. Another six people were denied permission to enter the state.<ref>{{cite web |title=6 arrests in Jalisco on first day of new isolation measures |url=https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/coronavirus/6-arrests-in-jalisco-on-first-day-of-new-isolation-measures/ |website=Mexico News Daily |accessdate=April 24, 2020 |date=April 22, 2020}}</ref> Two women were arrested in Quer\u00e9taro for attacking a health worker. They face up to three years in prison and a fine of 24,644 pesos (US $977).<ref>{{cite web |title=2 women arrested in Quer\u00e9taro for attacking health worker |url=https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/coronavirus/2-women-arrested-in-queretaro-for-attacking-health-worker/ |website=Mexico News Daily |accessdate=April 24, 2020 |date=April 23, 2020}}</ref> A field hospital with 854 beds is inaugurated in Mexico City; it should be fully operational on June 1.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mota |first1=J. I. |title=Ciudad de M\u00e9xico inaugura el primer hospital de campa\u00f1a para evitar el colapso sanitario |url=https://elpais.com/sociedad/2020-04-23/ciudad-de-mexico-inaugura-el-primer-hospital-de-campana-para-evitar-el-colapso-sanitario-por-el-coronavirus.html |website=EL PA\u00cdS |accessdate=April 24, 2020 |language=es |date=April 23, 2020|trans-title=Mexico City inaugurates the first field hospital to avoid health system collapse}}</ref>\n\nOn April 26, the [[Mexican Council of Businessmen|Mexican Council of Businessmen (CMN)]] and [[Inter-American Development Bank|IDB Invest]] announce a US$12 billion plan to provide credit to 30,000 micro-, small-, and medium-sized industries.<ref>{{cite web |title=BID Invest y el CMN lanzan plan de apoyo a 30,000 Mipymes en M\u00e9xico |url=https://www.msn.com/es-mx/dinero/noticias/bid-invest-y-el-cmn-lanzan-plan-de-apoyo-a-30000-mipymes-en-m%c3%a9xico/ar-BB13eiLF?ocid=mailsignout |website=www.msn.com |accessdate=April 29, 2020|language=es|trans-title=IDB Invest and CMN launch plan to support 30,000 MSMEs in Mexico}}</ref> AMLO opposes the plan, likening it to ''[[Fobaproa]],'' the 1995 bank-rescue plan that cost taxpayers billions.<ref>{{cite web |title=Acuerdo entre BID y empresarios equivale a corrupci\u00f3n: AMLO |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/politica/acuerdo-entre-bid-y-empresarios-equivale-corrupcion-amlo |website=El Universal |accessdate=April 29, 2020 |language=es |date=April 28, 2020}}</ref> PAN supports the plan.<ref>{{cite web |title=Acuerdo con el BID es ganar-ganar, dicen gobernadores del PAN |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/acuerdo-con-el-bid-es-ganar-ganar-dicen-gobernadores-del-pan |website=El Universal |accessdate=April 29, 2020 |language=es |date=April 27, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe death toll surpassed the 1,000 figure on April 23.<ref>{{cite web |title=1,000 new coronavirus cases in one day pushes total to more than 10,000 |url=https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/coronavirus/1000-new-coronavirus-cases-in-one-day/ |website=Mexico News Daily |accessdate=April 24, 2020 |date=April 23, 2020}}</ref> Tijuana expects its hospitals to run out of space over the weekend.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus pushes Tijuana hospitals toward saturation point |url=https://mexiconewsdaily.com/news/coronavirus/coronavirus-pushes-tijuana-hospitals-toward-saturation-point/ |website=Mexico News Daily |accessdate=April 24, 2020 |date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 29, eight public and three private hospitals in Mexico City stopped accepting COVID-19 patients due to a lack of space and ventilators. Mexico City Head of Government Claudia Scheinbaum said there were 54 hospitals with 1,500 beds available.<ref>{{cite web |title=Los principales hospitales de la CDMX comienzan a saturarse por COVID-19 |url=https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Los-principales-hospitales-de-la-CDMX-comienzan-a-saturarse-por-COVID-19-20200429-0018.html |website=El Informador |date=April 29, 2020 |language=es-ES|trans-title=The main hospitals in Mexico City begin to overcrowd due to COVID-19}}</ref> On the same day, I\u00f1aki Land\u00e1buru, president of the National Association of Wholesale Grocers (ANAM), threatened to stop the supermarkets' supply chain in the State of Mexico, Tabasco, Guerrero, Morelos, and Veracruz if safety measure are not enforced and if they are not provided with safety on highways. Land\u00e1buru said he believes food trucks are robbed by the organized crime who then redistribute the food for free in an attempt to demonstrate a false sense of solidarity among the population.<ref>{{cite web |title=Amagan abarroteros con dejar de surtir a 5 estados |url= https://www.excelsior.com.mx/nacional/amagan-abarroteros-con-dejar-de-surtir-a-5-estados/1378948 |website=Exc\u00e9lsior |date=April 29, 2020 |trans-title=Grocery store's suppliers threaten to stop supplying 5 states}}</ref>\n\n=== May ===\n\n==== 1 to 15 May ====\nOn 1 May, Mexico surpassed 20,000 infections of COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web |title=1 de Mayo. Suman mil 972 muertes por Covid-19 en M\u00e9xico, con 20,739 casos |url=https://www.eluniversal.com.mx/nacion/1-de-mayo-suman-mil-972-muertes-por-covid-19-en-mexico-con-20739-casos |website=El Universal |accessdate=May 2, 2020 |language=es |date=May 1, 2020}}</ref> ''Mexicanos contra la corrupci\u00f3n'' (Mexicans against corruption) alleged that L\u00e9on Manuel Bartlett, son of [[Manuel Bartlett]] the head of the [[Comisi\u00f3n Federal de Electricidad|Comisi\u00f3n Federal de Electricidad (CFE)]], fraudulently tried to sell overpriced ventilators to the Mexican Institute of Social Security (IMSS) in Hidalgo.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mota |first1=J. I. |title=Una investigaci\u00f3n revela que el hijo de un funcionario mexicano vendi\u00f3 al Gobierno ventiladores para la covid-19 a sobreprecio |url=https://elpais.com/internacional/2020-05-02/una-investigacion-revela-que-el-hijo-de-un-funcionario-mexicano-vendio-ventiladores-para-la-covid-19-a-sobreprecio-al-gobierno.html |website=EL PA\u00cdS |accessdate=May 2, 2020 |language=es |date=May 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 May, Mexico surpassed 2,000 deaths due to the COVID-19 pandemic.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus en M\u00e9xico: suman 2,061 muertos y 22,088 casos confirmados |url=https://www.infobae.com/america/mexico/2020/05/03/coronavirus-en-mexico-suman-2061-muertos-y-22088-casos-confirmados/ |website=infobae |accessdate=May 2, 2020 |language=es-ES}}</ref> At least forty Mexican and Guatemalan farm workers in [[COVID-19 pandemic in Canada|Canada]] contracted coronavirus, that according to the [[United Food and Commercial Workers]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Detectan a trabajadores agr\u00edcolas mexicanos con COVID-19 en Canad\u00e1 |url=https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Detectan-a-trabajadores-agricolas-mexicanos-con-COVID-19-en-Canada-20200502-0059.html |website=El Informador :: Noticias de Jalisco, M\u00e9xico, Deportes & Entretenimiento |accessdate=May 2, 2020 |language=es-ES}}</ref>\n\nOn May 3, IMSS published videos of the progress made on the construction of a field hospital in [[Aut\u00f3dromo Hermanos Rodr\u00edguez]] racetrack in Mexico City. The hospital is expected to go into operation on May 13.<ref>{{cite web |title=Instala IMSS \u2018hospital de expansi\u00f3n\u2019 en el Aut\u00f3dromo Hermanos Rodr\u00edguez para pacientes con Covid-19 |url=https://www.reporteindigo.com/reporte/instala-imss-hospital-de-expansion-en-el-autodromo-hermanos-rodriguez/ |website=Reporte Indigo |accessdate=May 3, 2020 |language=es-ES}}</ref>\n\nThe former presidential mansion [[Los Pinos]] opened as a shelter for IMSS health providers in Mexico City on May 4.<ref>{{cite web |title=Habilitan Los Pinos como albergue para m\u00e9dicos y enfermeras |url=https://www.informador.mx/mexico/Habilitan-Los-Pinos-como-albergue-para-medicos-y-enfermeras-20200504-0034.html |website=El Informador :: Noticias de Jalisco, M\u00e9xico, Deportes & Entretenimiento |accessdate=May 4, 2020 |language=es-ES}}</ref>\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n=== [[Secretariat of Health (Mexico)|SALUD]] reported Mexico totals ===\